<subSubSection id="1980FFE989F863417570C7E5992A8669" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F942866C3F654AB8356B102F4A29AB5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C13D183448D83F4228592822A8ACB9D" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="4C53E4907DB8C02CA89992B229849489" authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Rosa, Proshchalykin &amp; Halada" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychridium weii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weii">
<emphasis id="0B375568393E52ECECC2FDD486D27FBF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Hedychridium weii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(masculine noun in genitive) is dedicated to Na-sen 
<normalizedToken id="3FF11E298AFE23D2AF456267AC8B6AFD" originalValue="“Nelson”">&quot;Nelson&quot;</normalizedToken>
Wei (Guanghzou, China), for his contributions to the study of the 
<taxonomicName id="E0081343CB9AB7F63122A3CCBE22B5C2" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chrysididae</taxonomicName>
of Inner Mongolia and China and his kind support to the studies of the first author.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="083772C493BC78A2EDBEC39E062172D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="comparative diagnosis">
<paragraph id="47C4090EB8D65FCB421B5D1E32F701A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Comparative diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4122DD97E850F8582960BFED25200C83" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
We describe 
<taxonomicName id="BB361E4DE182AF5AFCEF4EB2FAFADC78" authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Rosa, Proshchalykin &amp; Halada" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychridium weii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weii">
<emphasis id="2F947F4A43FD2A566C90B15C04741E59" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Hedychridium weii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. in the 
<taxonomicName id="DD17692D38BC28B6F7CEB1A22EF8370A" genus="H." lsidName="H. femoratum" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="femoratum">
<emphasis id="9193C3388C7214C4ED1310EC9075E771" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">H. femoratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. It is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="85202FE40C4589413FC8B5CBF50E0B92" genus="H." lsidName="H. femoratum" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="femoratum">
<emphasis id="C99CCCCB454A630F351CF1FE7A09F416" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">H. femoratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for its general habitus, yet it is separated by sparser mesonotal punctures, shape of genital capsule (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A82735DF5F752030CC129AD4FA662E83" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Hedychridium weii sp. nov., male, holotype A habitus, dorsal view B head, frontal view C genital capsule D habitus, lateral view E right antenna, lateral view F metasoma, postero-lateral view G metasoma, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608683" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">16C</figureCitation>
), elongate shape of the black spot on metatibia (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0B0C83E736732F3FE6F12ACC0D2FAE11" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Hedychridium weii sp. nov., male, holotype A habitus, dorsal view B head, frontal view C genital capsule D habitus, lateral view E right antenna, lateral view F metasoma, postero-lateral view G metasoma, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.73549.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/608683" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">16F</figureCitation>
) and darker mesosoma colouration. It is separated from the other two newly- described species in this species group, 
<taxonomicName id="FC38666AB2DCE732E1EDD4CDAF75B9D7" genus="H." lsidName="H. splendens" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="splendens">
<emphasis id="DB9DB3F74F1C74D98FBD87F89E060B8C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">H. splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. and 
<taxonomicName id="3BCB10B6770106B14AC0BC482FD0210E" genus="H." lsidName="H. jacobsi" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" rank="species" species="jacobsi">
<emphasis id="362D99AA0BDF1F3D190EFB5ED514B59E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">H. jacobsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., by flagellomeres black, different genital capsule and different shape of black spots on metatibia.
</paragraph>
